[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_iln86")
reagent_id = "H2CO3"
title = "Carbonic acid"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]H₂CO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]62 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State:[/cell][cell]Liquid (solution)[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Weak acid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
CO₂ + H₂O → H₂CO₃
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Forms when carbon dioxide dissolves in water.
• Unstable — easily breaks down back into CO₂ and water.
• A weak acid compared to strong acids like HCl.
[b]Where it is found[/b]
• In carbonated drinks (soda).
• In natural waters containing dissolved CO₂.
• In the human body, where it helps regulate blood pH.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Important in the carbon cycle in nature.
• Responsible for the fizz in sparkling drinks.
[b]Safety[/b]
Weak acid and generally not dangerous in small concentrations."
